# .secretsignore — Whitelist patterns for known false-positive secrets
#
# One regex pattern per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
# Patterns are matched against file content during secret detection.
# If a match is found AND it also matches a pattern here, the commit is allowed.
#
# Example: Test fixture API keys
# AKIA_TEST_[A-Z0-9]{16}
# sk-test-[a-zA-Z0-9]{48}
#
# Example: Placeholder tokens in documentation
# EXAMPLE_API_KEY_[A-Z0-9]+
# your-api-key-here
#
# Example: Known safe base64 strings in config
# aGVsbG8gd29ybGQ=
